Sec. 71.048. APPEAL OF NOTICE OR ORDER. (a) A person who is
aggrieved by an order or notice of the department or whose property
is to be destroyed under an order or notice is entitled to appeal to
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 432 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

a district court of Travis County or to a district court of the
county in which the order or notice affects the person.
(b) In order to perfect an appeal under this section, the
person must file suit before the 11th day following the day on which
the person received the notice or order.
(c) A court may hear and determine an appeal under this section
during term or vacation.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1157, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

